article.headline: UNLV 67, Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 57
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- UNLV's Kevin Kruger had a game-high 23 points and Joe Darger added 11 points to lead the Rebels 67-57 over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi Sunday night. UNLV (8-2) only led 60-57 with 3:57 to play, but used a Wink Adams 3-pointer in scoring seven straight points to close the game. Adams added 11 points for the Rebels. Kruger keyed a 10-2 surge in the final 1:31 of the first half as the Rebels took advantage of a pair of technical fouls and went 10-for-10 from the foul line in breaking a 28-all tie. Kruger accounted for eight of the foul shots. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (4-3) got a team-high 14 points and nine rebounds from Chris Daniels. Manuel Johnson and Josh Washington added 10 points for the Islanders.
